and conceal membership in specific social, intellectual, and ideological communities. Attending to materials that go beyond music’s conventional limits, these chapters probe the role of music in commonplace books, health-maintenance and marriage manuals, rhetorical and theological treatises, and mathematical dictionaries. Ultimately, Austern illustrates how music was an indispensable frame of reference that became central to the fabric of life during a time of tremendous intellectual, social, and technological change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aMusiczEnglandy16th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMusiczEnglandy17th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMusic-England-16th century-History and criticism. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aShakespeare’s musical knowledge.  aStuart music.  aTudor music.  aclassical tradition.  aepistemologies of music.  ahistory of learning and scholarship.  amusic as a liberal art.  amusical discourse.  amusical ontology.  aphilosophy of music.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831106930960 cprintz978022670159240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226704678423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226704678/original  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6